-- Siemens Eyes Bigger Wind Power Market Share, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   J e r e m y   v a n   L o o n
-- 2010-10-11T05:03:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/siemens-eyes-bigger-wind-power-market-share-handelsblatt-says.html
Siemens AG  wants to boost its share
of the wind turbine market and surpass market leaders General
Electric Co. and Vestas Wind Systems A/S,  Handelsblatt  reported.  Siemens is counting on expanding turbine sales in China and
the U.S. to help the German company increase its 5.9 percent
share of the global market, the newspaper said, citing Rene
Umlauf, who heads Siemens wind business.  To contact the reporters on this story:
 Jeremy van Loon  in Berlin at 
 jvanloon@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  